                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1931-03-31T14:05:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1931-03-31T12:00:00-05:00" when="1931-03-31"
                        >undated</date>].<lb/>[Received March 31, 1931—2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Tropical Radio reports Managua destroyed by earthquake this morning and now
                    burning. U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Rochester</hi> probably sail tonight for
                    Corinto. U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Sacramento</hi> standing by here. Navy plane
                    could be despatched tomorrow from Canal to investigate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
